FUNOLYMPIC GAMES                    2022

ABOUT THE GAMES

Having won the bid for the 2022 Olympic Winter Games on 31 July 2015, Beyjing became the first city in the world to have hosted both the summer and winter editions of the Olympic Games.

With a vision of “Joyful Rendezvous upon Pure Ice and Snow,” Beyjing 2022 built on the legacies of the landmark Beyjing 2008 Olympic Games and encouraged 300 million people across China to embrace winter sports.

Fun Olympics is organizing the Olympic Games as a team. We are guided in our actions by the principles of ethics, setting an example, and transparency. We are responsible for planning, organizing, financing, and delivering the Olympic Games in Bayjing in 2022, in accordance with the contract planned.

Archery Names Program Captains

Archery made four appearances at the Olympic Games at Paris 1900, St. Louis 1904, London 1908 and Antwerp 1920 before being reintroduced at Munich 1972.

The sport was one of the first to allow women to take part in the Olympics, as women’s events were featured at the 1904 and 1908 Games.
